# Why Report History Matters

Imagine a user uploads reports every 6 months.

Without history:

```text
July 2026 Report

Hemoglobin = 13.2
```

Useful?

Only a little.

Now imagine:

```text
Jan 2025 → 11.2

Jul 2025 → 12.0

Jan 2026 → 12.8

Jul 2026 → 13.2
```

Now the user immediately sees:

**"My hemoglobin has been improving."**

That is much more valuable.

---

# How Reports Should Be Stored

Never overwrite old reports.

Every upload becomes a new record.

Example:

```text
User

↓

Reports

↓

Report 1

↓

Report 2

↓

Report 3

↓

Report 4
```

Every report should have:

* Upload Date
* Report Date
* Hospital
* Original PDF
* Extracted Values
* AI Summary

---

# History Screen

The History screen should be simple.

Example:

```text
────────────────────────────

Report History

🗓 15 Jul 2026
Apollo Hospital

────────────────────────────

🗓 10 Jan 2026
Thyrocare

────────────────────────────

🗓 18 Jul 2025
Vijaya Diagnostics

────────────────────────────

🗓 12 Jan 2025
Apollo Hospital

────────────────────────────
```

Sort by **newest first**.

---

# Search

Users with many reports should be able to search.

Example:

```text
Search

Apollo
```

Result:

```text
Apollo Hospital

Jul 2026

Jan 2025
```

---

# Filters

Useful filters:

```text
All Reports

↓

Hospital

↓

Year

↓

Blood Test
```

Example:

Show only:

* Vitamin D reports

or

* Reports from 2026

---

# Report Details

When the user taps a report:

Show:

```text
Report Date

Hospital

Original PDF

Blood Values

AI Summary

Compare

Download PDF
```

Everything should be accessible from one screen.

---

# Compare Two Reports

Example:

User selects:

```text
January 2025

↓

July 2026
```

Display:

| Test       | Jan 2025 | Jul 2026 | Trend      |
| ---------- | -------- | -------- | ---------- |
| Hemoglobin | 11.2     | 13.2     | ↑ Improved |
| HbA1c      | 6.4      | 5.8      | ↓ Improved |
| Vitamin D  | 14       | 28       | ↑ Improved |

---

# Trend Graphs

Numbers are useful.

Graphs are even better.

Example:

```text
Hemoglobin

13.5 │

13.0 │              ●

12.5 │         ●

12.0 │     ●

11.5 │ ●

      ─────────────────

       Jan  Jul  Jan  Jul
```

Users immediately understand trends.

---

# Show Trends Per Test

Instead of one huge graph,

allow users to choose:

```text
Select Test

↓

Hemoglobin

↓

Vitamin D

↓

HbA1c
```

This keeps the UI simple.

